Parliament, Wednesday, 27 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Communications, having revised its first-term programme due to Parliament’s tight schedule, will tomorrow, 28 February 2019, shortlist 24 candidates to be interviewed to fill the eight vacancies at the board of the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC). Also as part of changes to the programme, the committee will no longer conduct exit interviews with those who resigned from the current board. The names of shortlisted candidates will be published on Parliament’s website for public comments and interviews will be conducted from 5 to 7 March 2019. The shortlisting will take place as follows:
	Date: Thursday, 28 February 2019
	Venue: Committee Room V475
	Time: 10:00 ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COMMUNICATIONS, PROF HLEGIWE MKHIZE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact media officer: Name: Mr Justice MolafoTel: 021 403 8444Cell: 081 424 7481Email: jmolafo@parliament.gov.za The Bill of Rights guarantees the right to assemble, demonstrate, picket and present petitions as long as this is done in a peaceful way and the protesters are unarmed.Read more